{
  "texts": [
    "Table 3 summarizes some representative underwater datasets used for underwater object detection tasks in recent years.",
    "The Brackish dataset was first proposed and made publicly available by Pedersen et al. (2019).",
    "This dataset consists of 14518 frames of images, with the original data being video data.",
    "The Brackish dataset contains 25613 annotations belonging to six categories: big fish, small fish, crab, jellyfish, shrimp, and starfish.",
    "Figure 1 shows the sample frame image for each category in the Brackish dataset."
  ]
}